BASICS — First Steps in Empire

YOUR FIRST SESSION
  When you log in, type commands at the prompt.  Most commands
  accept abbreviated names (census = cens, designate = des, etc.).

  Start by surveying your territory:
    census *          see all your sectors
    resource *        see mineral deposits
    nation            see your treasury and stats
    map *             see a map of your territory
    update            see when the next update runs

BUILD YOUR ECONOMY
  Food comes first.  Without food, civilians starve.
    1. Find a sector with high fert:    resource *
    2. Designate it as agribusiness:    des X,Y a
    3. Set food threshold in capital:   threshold food 0,0 2000
    4. Set threshold elsewhere:         threshold food * 30

  Then develop production:
    - Iron mine (m) + LCM factory (j) → light construction materials
    - LCM + libraries (l) → education
    - LCM + tech center (t) + research (r) → technology
    - Gold mine (g) → dust → treasury income

GROW YOUR TERRITORY
    explore 0,0 j civ 10    send civilians to claim new sectors
    explore 0,0 jj civ 5    two sectors east

BUILD A MILITARY
    des 1,-3 e              designate an enlistment center
    (wait for updates until it reaches 60% efficiency)
    demobilize 1,-3 100     move auto-enlisted mil to reserve
    enlist 0,0 50           place reserve troops in capital

CONNECT SECTORS
    distribute * 0,0        all sectors distribute to capital
    threshold food * 30     each sector keeps 30 food minimum
    threshold food 0,0 2000 capital keeps 2000 food

